# Commit After Changes

After making code changes, always create a git commit before ending your turn.

- Follow the repo's commit message style: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `chore:`
- Write a concise message (1-2 sentences) explaining **why**, not just what
- Group related changes into a single commit; unrelated changes get separate commits
- Never commit files that contain secrets (`.env`, credentials, API keys)
